message.entry: Parameter names must be a string or character vector.
Valid parameter names are RatioType, OverlapThreshold, and NumStrongest.
The RatioType value must be 'Union' or 'Min'.
The NumStrongest value must be a positive scalar integer or inf.
The NumStrongest value must be a positive scalar integer or inf, or a vector of positive integers.
When the NumStrongest value is a vector with more than one element, number of elements must equal the number of categories in the input labels.
When the NumStrongest value is a vector, the input labels must be categorical.
입력 레이블이 숫자형 값인 경우 NumStrongest의 값은 고정 크기 스칼라여야 합니다.
The input labels must be categorical values created with a fixed set of categories. For example, labels = categorical(data, valueset).
The input bbox must be an M-by-4 gpuArray. GPU processing only supports axis-aligned bounding boxes.
The input bbox and score must both be gpuArray objects.
